 reintroduce the Zimbabwe dollar and accelerate plans to repay the country's debt, in a bid to revive the battered economy. September 10, 2018 In "News" Zimbabwe’s President Emmerson Mnangagwa cut short his annual vacation Wednesday to try to resolve an impasse with doctors who have been on strike for a month, a government spokesman said. January 2, 2019 In "News" Zimbabwe on Friday reported its first coronavirus case, a man who returned to his home in the tourist resort town of Victoria Falls from Britain at the weekend. "The is the first case of Covid-19 in Zimbabwe," said Health Minister Obadiah Moyo on state television ZTV. "The patient is a… March 20, 2020 In "Coronavirus Updates"